@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Ice_Dungeon" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  The game presents a three-dimensional view of the various corridors in the
dungeon, you can click in this display to move forward, turn left or right,
climb up or down (if you face a ladder) a level. To move forward, click in
the center of the display, to turn right or left, click either at the right
or left from the center of the display. If you are unsure about this procedure
just experiment by clicking anywhere in the display and see what happens...
I am sure you will get the hang of it very quickly!

  You can also move by clicking on the buttons located on the right in the
game window. The "N", "S", "E" and "W" buttons will turn you in the North,
South, East or West directions respectively. Hint: if you are facing north
and click on the "S" button, it will make you turn to the south, which is
quicker than clicking two times in the left (or right) area in the display
(and you make one move instead of two, this may make a difference between
completing the game or not!). The "move" button will make you move forward.

  If you are on a space where a ladder is located, depending on where it goes
(up or down) a button marked "Up" or "down" will appear. Clicking on that
button will change the level you are at (you can also click on the "ceiling"
or "ground" area, if you want to climb up a level or descend one level). Note
that you MUST face the ladder in order to change levels.

  If you are lost on a particular level, you can click on the "map" button,
this will display a window showing a map of all the explored area of that
level. The smiling face icon represents your current position. Note that once
the map is shown, the game waits until you click on the map window's close
button. Beware! Each time you look at the map, time passes and if you look at
a map too often, you may freeze!

  Another thing to watch carefully is the "thermometer" icon displayed between
the 3D view and the game buttons on the right. The more you move, the lower the
mercury will get. When the mercury is very low (i.e.: very cold temperature)
you are near freezing, so better find out the talismans and go to the exit
before... you know what!

  A talisman will only show when it's at the next space in front of you. So
it's very important that you explore as much as possible all the corridors and
dead-ends of the dungeon. Who knows? One of the needed talisman may hide in an
area you thought wasn't worth searching...

  If you see a talisman, just walk on the space occupied by it. When you have
the two talismans, hurry up to the exit door, especially if the thermometer's
mercury is very low! Note that you @{b}must@{ub} face the exit door in order to get
out.

  Have fun!

